Algorithm to Calculate Simple Interest
1.Start.
2.Input the principal amount P, rate of interest R, and time in years T.
3.Use the formula: SI=(PxRxT)/100
4.Print the calculated value of SI.
5.Stop.

PSEUDOCODE:
START
    INPUT P, R, T
    SI ← (P × R × T) / 100
    PRINT SI
END

FLOWCHART:
A[Start] --> B[Input P, R, T]
    B --> C[Calculate SI = (P × R × T) / 100]
    C --> D[Print SI]
    D --> E[Stop]
